car.orientor.client.wfio.obj
Class ObjIO

java.lang.Object
  car.orientor.client.wfio.obj.ObjIO

public abstract class ObjIO
extends java.lang.Object

Handles the parsing of .obj files, and converts them into ObjWireFrames. Doesn't support writing them, since that's not quite possible in JavaScript (as far as I care, anyways).

Author:
Joshua

createFromURL

public static void createFromURL(ObjWireFrame dest,
                                 java.lang.String url,
                                 com.google.gwt.user.client.Command onLoad)
Starts the asynchronous request for the .obj file and parses the results. The results are eventually stored in the supplied ObjWireFrame. Once the .obj file is finished loading and parsing.

Parameters:
url - the URL of the .obj file to load.
onLoad - the Command to execute when it's finished loading.
See Also:
